TITLE: Declaring a Wasp Query (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Declares a query named `getTasks` within the `main.wasp` file for a TypeScript project. It specifies the implementation function (`getTasks`) imported from `@src/queries.ts` and links it to the `Task` entity for automatic cache invalidation and updates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/versioned_docs/version-0.14.0/tutorial/05-queries.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: wasp
CODE:
```
```wasp title="main.wasp"
// ...

query getTasks {
  // Specifies where the implementation for the query function is.
  // The path `@src/queries` resolves to `src/queries.ts`.
  // No need to specify an extension.
  fn: import { getTasks } from "@src/queries",
  // Tell Wasp that this query reads from the `Task` entity. Wasp will
  // automatically update the results of this query when tasks are modified.
  entities: [Task]
}
```
