TITLE: Exporting Custom userSignupFields Validator in Wasp Server (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet exports userSignupFields, leveraging defineUserSignupFields from wasp/server/auth for server-side validation. It enforces that the address field is a non-empty string of minimum length 5, throwing user-friendly errors on invalid input. Ensure that this file aligns with the import in main.wasp.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/versioned_docs/version-0.12.0/auth/overview.md#2025-04-22_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { defineUserSignupFields } from 'wasp/server/auth'

export const userSignupFields = defineUserSignupFields({
  address: async (data) => {
    const address = data.address
    if (typeof address !== 'string') {
      throw new Error('Address is required')
    }
    if (address.length < 5) {
      throw new Error('Address must be at least 5 characters long')
    }
    return address
  },
})
```

