TITLE: Defining AuthIdentity Entity in Prisma for Wasp Internal Authentication
DESCRIPTION: Shows the schema for the 'AuthIdentity' model in Prisma. This model stores the user's credentials for various authentication providers (e.g., email, Google). Each identity is uniquely identified by provider name and provider user ID, and is related to an 'Auth' entity. Most fields are managed by Wasp internally.
