TITLE: Defining Custom User Signup Fields (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript version of the previous snippet demonstrates how to define custom user signup fields. It shows the process of adding an 'address' field with validation logic using the defineUserSignupFields function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/versioned_docs/version-0.14.0/auth/overview.md#2025-04-22_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { defineUserSignupFields } from 'wasp/server/auth'

export const userSignupFields = defineUserSignupFields({
  address: async (data) => {
    const address = data.address
    if (typeof address !== 'string') {
      throw new Error('Address is required')
    }
    if (address.length < 5) {
      throw new Error('Address must be at least 5 characters long')
    }
    return address
  },
})
```

