TITLE: Implementing Query Logic in Node.js with Prisma SDK
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to implement the query logic for fetching lists and cards using the Prisma SDK in a Node.js environment within a Wasp application.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/blog/2021-12-02-waspello.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export const getListsAndCards = async (args, context) => {
  // Only authenticated users can execute this query.
  if (!context.user) { throw new HttpError(403) }

  return context.entities.List.findMany({
    // We want to make sure user can access only their own cards.
    where: { user: { id: context.user.id } },
    include: { cards: true }
  })
}
```

