TITLE: Updating getTasks Query with Authentication Check in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Modifies the getTasks query to check for user authentication and retrieve only the logged-in user's tasks. Throws a 401 error if the user is not authenticated.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/versioned_docs/version-0.11.8/tutorial/07-auth.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import HttpError from '@wasp/core/HttpError.js'

export const getTasks = async (args, context) => {
  if (!context.user) {
    throw new HttpError(401)
  }
  return context.entities.Task.findMany({
    where: { user: { id: context.user.id } },
    orderBy: { id: 'asc' },
  })
}
```

