TITLE: Defining Auth and User Entities in Wasp 0.11.X  Wasp with PSL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how authentication and user entities are declared in a Wasp 0.11.X project. Dependencies include PSL for entities (Prisma Schema Language); providers like GitHub require their own configuration. The 'auth' section configures user and external auth associations. Inputs are classic Wasp/PSL entity definitions. Outputs: a project manifest describing app meta, supported login methods, and ORM models for users and social login. Limitation: developers must manage password/email fields and relational associations manually.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/versioned_docs/version-0.13.0/migrate-from-0-11-to-0-12.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

