TITLE: Implementing userSignupFields in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: TypeScript implementation of the userSignupFields object that validates the address field during user signup, ensuring it meets requirements before saving to the database.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/versioned_docs/version-0.14.0/auth/overview.md#2025-04-22_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { defineUserSignupFields } from 'wasp/server/auth'

export const userSignupFields = defineUserSignupFields({
  address: async (data) => {
    const address = data.address
    if (typeof address !== 'string') {
      throw new Error('Address is required')
    }
    if (address.length < 5) {
      throw new Error('Address must be at least 5 characters long')
    }
    return address
  },
})
```

