TITLE: Defining the Internal `AuthIdentity` Entity in Wasp's Prisma Schema
DESCRIPTION: Details the Prisma schema for Wasp's internal `AuthIdentity` entity. It stores credentials for different authentication providers (e.g., 'email', 'google'), linking them via `authId` to the `Auth` entity. Includes `providerName`, `providerUserId`, `providerData` (JSON string containing provider-specific data like hashed passwords), and a relation to the `Auth` entity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/versioned_docs/version-0.14.0/auth/entities/entities.md#2025-04-22_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: prisma
CODE:
```
```prisma
model AuthIdentity {
  providerName   String
  providerUserId String
  providerData   String @default("{}")
  authId         String
  auth           Auth   @relation(fields: [authId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)

  @@id([providerName, providerUserId])
}
```
```

