TITLE: Full App Configuration Structure in Wasp
DESCRIPTION: Provides a comprehensive overview of the structure of the `app` declaration in Wasp. It includes the required fields `wasp.version` and `title`, the optional `head` field, and placeholders for other configuration dictionaries like `auth`, `client`, `server`, `db`, `emailSender`, and `webSocket`. Each of these dictionaries allows for further customization of specific application aspects detailed in separate documentation sections.
