TITLE: Defining Entities for Automatic CRUD - Wasp Language
DESCRIPTION: Defines a `Task` entity in the Wasp language, specifying fields and their data types using the PSL (Prisma Schema Language) block. This forms the foundation for CRUD operations and requires Wasp CLI and a database (configured with Prisma) as dependencies. The expected inputs are entity field definitions, and outputs are migrated database schema and entity availability throughout the app.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/versioned_docs/version-0.13.0/data-model/crud.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: wasp
CODE:
```
entity Task {=psl\n  id          Int @id @default(autoincrement())\n  description String\n  isDone      Boolean\npsl=}
```

