TITLE: Using routes Object for Different Route Types in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use the routes object to build links for different types of routes, including a root route without parameters and a detail route with parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wasp-lang/wasp/blob/main/web/versioned_docs/version-0.12.0/advanced/links.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { routes } from 'wasp/client/router'

const linkToRoot = routes.RootRoute.build()
const linkToTask = routes.DetailRoute.build({ params: { id: 1 } })
```

